main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects (UFOs) over Webb AFB and Sweetwater, Texas, on March 29, 1965.
interesting points: Witnesses reported seeing two circular reddish bright objects in the sky, which emitted no sound and were difficult to see against the clouds., The objects were confirmed by air observers who noted they lit up the cockpit, indicating an interaction with the aircraft., A prominent feature of the sightings was that the objects flashed on and off rapidly before separating., One object was described as a short cigar shape with a greenish light and a trail, observed for up to 30 seconds., Multiple military personnel and civilians witnessed these events, with reports submitted to military authorities.
sighted object: two circular reddish bright objects and a greenish light object
